<h1>About Tech Insights</h1>
<p>Welcome to <strong>Tech Insights</strong> - a minimalist tech blog focused on software engineering, systems programming, and web development. My mission is to share practical knowledge and insights that help developers build better, faster, and more maintainable software.</p>
<h2>About Alex Chen</h2>
<p>I’m a software engineer with 8+ years of experience building high-performance web applications and distributed systems. I specialize in full-stack JavaScript development, systems programming with Rust and Go, and cloud architecture.</p>
<h3>My Journey</h3>
<p>My passion for technology started early, but it was during my computer science studies that I truly fell in love with the art of writing clean, efficient code. Over the years, I’ve had the privilege of working on everything from high-traffic web applications to low-level systems programming.</p>
<p><strong>Current Role</strong>: Senior Software Engineer at TechFlow Solutions, where I lead the development of cloud-native applications serving 100,000+ users daily.</p>
<h3>Technical Expertise</h3>
<p><strong>Programming Languages:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Primary</strong>: JavaScript, TypeScript, Python, Rust</li>
<li><strong>Secondary</strong>: Go, SQL, Bash, C++</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Frameworks &amp; Tools:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Frontend</strong>: React, Vue.js, Svelte</li>
<li><strong>Backend</strong>: Node.js, FastAPI, Axum, Gin</li>
<li><strong>Cloud</strong>: AWS, GCP, Docker, Kubernetes</li>
<li><strong>Development</strong>: VS Code, Git, CI/CD pipelines</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Specializations:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Web Performance Optimization</li>
<li>Distributed Systems Architecture</li>
<li>API Design &amp; Development</li>
<li>DevOps &amp; Infrastructure</li>
<li>Technical Writing &amp; Documentation</li>
</ul>
<h3>Open Source &amp; Community</h3>
<p>I’m passionate about giving back to the developer community:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Maintainer</strong> of <a href="https://github.com/alexchen/web-perf-toolkit">web-perf-toolkit</a> - Performance monitoring utilities</li>
<li><strong>Creator</strong> of <a href="https://github.com/alexchen/rust-api-templates">rust-api-templates</a> - Production-ready API templates</li>
<li><strong>Contributor</strong> to Eleventy core, Prism.js, and various npm packages</li>
</ul>
<h3>Speaking &amp; Writing</h3>
<p>I enjoy sharing knowledge through:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Conference talks</strong> on web performance and Rust programming</li>
<li><strong>Technical articles</strong> in industry publications</li>
<li><strong>Mentoring</strong> junior developers and career changers</li>
<li><strong>This blog</strong> where I explore practical programming topics</li>
</ul>
<h2>About This Blog</h2>
<p><strong>Tech Insights</strong> was born from my belief that technical content should be:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Practical</strong>: Real-world examples you can apply immediately</li>
<li><strong>Accessible</strong>: Complex topics explained clearly</li>
<li><strong>Performance-focused</strong>: Fast loading, minimal dependencies</li>
<li><strong>Community-driven</strong>: Encouraging discussion and learning</li>
</ul>
<h3>What You’ll Find Here</h3>
<p>I write about topics I’m passionate about and encounter in my daily work:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Web Development</strong>: JavaScript/TypeScript, performance optimization, modern frameworks</li>
<li><strong>Systems Programming</strong>: Rust, Go, concurrency, memory management</li>
<li><strong>DevOps</strong>: Cloud architecture, CI/CD, monitoring, scalability</li>
<li><strong>Career Development</strong>: Growing as a software engineer, technical leadership</li>
</ul>
<h3>Technology Stack</h3>
<p>This blog itself reflects my values:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Static Site Generator</strong>: Eleventy (11ty) for speed and simplicity</li>
<li><strong>Styling</strong>: Sass with mobile-first responsive design</li>
<li><strong>Syntax Highlighting</strong>: Prism.js supporting multiple languages</li>
<li><strong>Performance</strong>: &lt;2 second load times, optimized images, minimal JavaScript</li>
<li><strong>Accessibility</strong>: WCAG 2.1 AA compliant, screen reader friendly</li>
</ul>
